procstep.procdesc:
Note: Sugg's county estimates of subsurface tile drainage extents are from 1) his revised estimates for the majority of the counties in the Midwest and for the remaining counties, 2) the 1992 National Resources Inventory (NRI) data. Sugg's data table includes a "Source" field that indicates whether his final county estimate of subsurface tile drainage extent represents the 1992 NRI county total or his revised county estimate. In developing this dataset, the counties for which Sugg obtained areas of the subsurface tile drains from NRI were geoprocessed separately to exclude federally-owned land because NRI surveys do not include federal land. 

The 11 individual process steps can be summarized into 5 major steps:

a) created the geospatial datasets that was used to allocate both the 1992 NRI and Sugg's  revised estimate of subsurface tile drainage extent for Midwest states (Process steps 1-4); 

b) created the geospatial datasets that were used to allocate the 1992 NRI's estimates (Process steps 5-6); 

c) created the geospatial datasets that were used to allocate Sugg's revised estimates  (Process steps 7-8); 

d) merged the geospatial datasets created in Process steps 6 and 8 to create the final geospatial dataset representing potentially drained land (Process step 9); and 

e) calculated the cell values to be assigned to the grid cells characterized as potentially drained land and created the final raster of the subsurface tile drainage extent (Process steps 10-11).
